AN ACT relating to housing; revising provisions which prohibit
certain insurers from discriminating based on the breed of
a dog at certain properties; revising provisions relating to
the supportive housing grant program implemented by the
Housing Division of the Department of Business and
Industry; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law prohibits an insurer from refusing to issue, cancelling, refusing to
2 renew or increasing the premium or rate for certain policies of insurance on the sole
3 basis of the specific breed or mixture of breeds of a dog that is harbored or owned
4 on an applicable property unless, pursuant to the public health laws of this State,
5 the particular dog: (1) is known to be dangerous or vicious; or (2) has been declared
6 to be dangerous or vicious. (NRS 687B.383) Section 1 of this bill expands this
7 prohibition to include a policy of insurance which covers a multi-family residential
8 dwelling.
9 Existing law requires the Housing Division of the Department of Business and
10 Industry, subject to the availability of funds, to develop and implement a supportive
11 housing grant program for the purpose of awarding grants for the development of
12 supportive housing and the provision of supportive housing services. (NRS
13 319.600, 319.610) Section 2 of this bill requires any recipient of a grant for
14 supportive housing to agree in writing to allow a tenant in the supportive housing to
15 keep at least one pet.
